data.title: Group 038: R-M269 LK=[K]-CV-EO-KO-MO-MP-PY-QP-QR-UO-XZ
data.text:
ROGER PARKE (NJ 1682) LINE: A large number of the test participants to date are descendants of the Roger PARKE (NJ 1682) line, so identified by the Parke Society as LK=K. The following test participants all show a genetic connection to this line, though some do not have a clear paper trail back to Roger PARKE (NJ 1682). Dr. Roger PARKE was christened in June 1648 in the Cartmel Priory Church, Cartmel, Lancashire Co., England, the son of Allen PARKE & wife Elizabeth. Dr. Roger PARKE married Ann PATISON while still in England and moved to New Jersey ca. 1682. There are three known children of Dr. Roger PARKE and Ann PATISON: Anne PARKE b. ca. 1676 & John PARKE b. ca. 1678, both born while still in England, and Roger PARKE II, b. 25 June 1684 in Burlington Co., New Jersey.
